  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-SI-01 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package declares ed25519 as the signing algorithm and carries a valid SHA-256 content hash, but the signature value itself has been omitted — leaving the artifact in a partially-signed state that cannot be verified for structural integrity (W-SI-01).",
